The experiment `bow_20260514_151207_run_01` using a Bag of Words (BoW) architecture with TF-IDF vectorization achieved a reasonable performance, as indicated by an F1 score of 0.7188 and accuracy of 0.775. The use of TF-IDF for feature extraction likely contributed to the model's ability to capture important terms in the text data effectively. However, the experiment did not explore different n-gram settings or other hyperparameters such as regularization strength (`logreg_c`), which could potentially improve performance further. For the next run, consider experimenting with different n-gram ranges (e.g., `ngram_max` > 1) and varying the `logreg_c` parameter to see if these changes can lead to better model accuracy and F1 scores. Additionally, exploring other vectorization techniques or feature selection methods might also yield improvements.